Electronics Store

Technologies: Core Java, Servlets, JSP, JDBC, HTML, CSS
Database: Oracle
Server: Apache Tomcat (WAR / external servlet container)

Overview

Electronics Store is a simple e-commerce web application with two modules:

Admin module

Admin login

Add product

View / Edit / Delete products

Logout

Customer module

Customer registration and login

Browse / View products

Purchase products (order flow)

Logout

The project uses plain JDBC to connect to an Oracle database and is packaged as a WAR for deployment on Tomcat.

Tech stack

Java 11+ / Java 17

JSP, Servlet API

JDBC (Oracle)

Maven (build)

Apache Tomcat 9/10

HTML, CSS

Repository structure
electronics-store/
├─ src/
│  ├─ main/
│  │  ├─ java/                # com.yourorg.* servlets, DAOs, models
│  │  └─ webapp/
│  │     ├─ WEB-INF/
│  │     │  ├─ web.xml
│  │     │  └─ lib/           # optional: place JDBC jar when packaging
│  │     └─ views/            # JSPs (login.jsp, products.jsp, admin/*)
├─ db/
│  ├─ schema.sql
│  └─ seed.sql
├─ pom.xml
├─ README.md
└─ .gitignore

Requirements

JDK 11 or later (Java 17 recommended)

Maven

Apache Tomcat 9 or 10

Oracle DB (local or remote)

Oracle JDBC driver (ojdbc8.jar / ojdbc11.jar) — not included in repo
